# Monday Webhook Validation

## Patterns to Flag

- HTTP handlers for Monday webhooks that do not respond to subscription challenge requests (echo `challenge` from body)
- Hardcoded or logged full webhook URLs in source (reusable endpoints that should stay secret)
- Processing webhook POST bodies without verifying signing secret / HMAC or equivalent when Monday provides it
- Public webhook routes with no authentication, IP allowlisting, or shared-secret validation beyond challenge
- Handlers that run business logic without checking `event.type` or supported event names (treating all payloads the same)

## What to Do

- On webhook setup, parse JSON body; if `challenge` is present, return it in the response body as Monday expects
- Store webhook URL configuration in environment or secure config, not in committed source
- Verify signatures using the signing secret from environment variables when the platform supports it
- Reject unknown event types early; validate minimal schema before side effects
- Use HTTPS endpoints only; avoid echoing secrets or tokens in logs

## Exceptions

- Documentation snippets using `https://example.com/webhook` style placeholders
- Local tunnel URLs in `.env.example` without real hostnames
- Integration tests that mock the challenge flow explicitly
